sentences: David Fonseca (Portuguese pronunciation: [dɐˈvid fõˈsekɐ], born on 14 June 1973, in Leiria) is a Portuguese musician, singer-songwriter and photographer.
He is recognized for his successful music career as a member of Silence 4 and, since 2003, as a solo artist.
Between 2004 and 2006, he was also part of the Humanos tribute project.
He also attended Escola Superior de Belas Artes de Lisboa between 1992 and 1994.
On December 27th, 2019, married the model, actress, and presenter Ana Sofia Martins.
They first released the unpredictable Silence Becomes It, in June 1998 that was a huge success at the time, selling 250,000 copies (the equivalent to six platinum records).
Two years after the "phenomenon" the second album was released, Only Pain Is Real, in July 2000, selling approximately 100,000 copies to this day.
Throughout 2000, Silence 4 went on their last tour.
In 2001, the band entered an undetermined hiatus, that still remains.
In his first solo work Sing Me Something New, recorded in 2003, Fonseca sang and played nearly all the instruments, exploring a totally new environment of sounds on his own.

Our Hearts Will Beat As One, his second solo album, is said by Fonseca himself to be "scarily personal" and was only released in the fall of 2005 because of the other projects that Fonseca was involved in between his two albums.

In October 2007, his third original album, Dreams in Colour, was released and the first single was Superstars II, a song that obtained substantial airplay due to a cellphone campaign that adopted the single.
In July 2009, the first single ("A Cry 4 Love") was finally released to the public.
The new album, Between Waves, was out on 2 November 2009.
Fonseca's fourth album entitled Seasons:Rising was released 21 March 2012.
The first single What Life Is For came up on 4 February 2012.
In 2004, David joined a new project called Humanos.
The idea behind it was to record some unpublished songs by the famous Portuguese artist, a singer-songwriter, from the 1980s, António Variações.
Thus, the CD and DVD with the recorded Coliseums’ live concerts, which was released on November 2006, marked the end of the Humanos project.

Our Hearts Will Beat As One, his second solo album, is said by Fonseca himself to be "scarily personal" and was only released in the fall of 2005 because of the other projects that Fonseca was involved in between his two albums.
Fonseca's solo career kicked off the 21st century with a different sound from Silence 4.
On December 27th, 2019, married the model, actress, and presenter Ana Sofia Martins.
To complete this great year for the band, which played at most of the Portuguese Summer festivals, they closed the world-famous exhibition Expo '98 in Lisbon, playing for about 50 thousand people.

Later in the same year, in December, Silence 4 was the first national band to sell out at Pavilhão Atlântico, performing to an astonishing 18,000-strong crowd, only 6 months after the release of their first album.
Two years after the "phenomenon" the second album was released, Only Pain Is Real, in July 2000, selling approximately 100,000 copies to this day.
The first single was Someone That Cannot Love which debuted on about 150 Portuguese radio stations in a coordinated release: they were all played on 10 March at midnight.
Our Hearts Will Beat As One was critically acclaimed by the media and was considered pop album of the year in Portugal, even before the end of the year.
The album went straight to No. 1 on the National Sales Chart and reached Gold status on its first week of sales.
On the same day, Fonseca's online community, Amazing Cats Club started working.
The eponymous album scored an impressive quintuple platinum, staying for weeks at No. 1.
There was also another memorable performance, in front of a crowd of 40,000 people, at the "Sudoeste" Portuguese Festival, in the year 2005.
